%sql

select case when rrv.stars in ('1', '2') then 'bad_review' 
            when rrv.stars in ('4', '5') then 'good_review'
            else '' end as review_ctr
      , rs.subcategory
      , count(*) as cnt
from restaurants_review rrv
inner join restaurants_subcategory rs on rrv.business_id = rs.business_id
where rrv.stars <> '3'
group by case when rrv.stars in ('1', '2') then 'bad_review' 
            when rrv.stars in ('4', '5') then 'good_review'
            else '' end
      , rs.subcategory
order by cnt desc
limit 10
